description._content: Collection: NASA Marshall Space Flight Center Collection Name of Image: Laser Geodynamics Satellite I Full Description: The LAGEOS I (Laser Geodynamics Satellite) was developed and launched by the Marshall Space Flight Center on May 4, 1976 from Vandenberg Air Force Base, California . The two-foot diameter satellite orbited the Earth from pole to pole and measured the movements of the Earth's surface.
